decisionPoints.title: Monthly main income less finances, rent
decisionPoints.description: Decision Point 959 calculates the monthly uncommitted income by taking the main income and subtracting Ongoing financial commitments and rent expenses.

decisionPoints.title: Monthly identified income less finances, rent
decisionPoints.description: Decision Point 960 calculates the monthly uncommitted income by taking all Ongoing identified income and subtracting Ongoing financial commitments and rent expenses.

decisionPoints.title: Monthly identified income less finances, rent, essential spend
decisionPoints.description: Decision Point 961 calculates the monthly uncommitted income by taking all Ongoing identified income and subtracting Ongoing financial commitments, rent & essential expenses.

decisionPoints.title: Monthly identified income less finances, rent, essential, fixed discretionary spend
decisionPoints.description: Decision Point 962 calculates the monthly uncommitted income by taking all Ongoing identified income and subtracting Ongoing financial commitments, rent, essential & fixed discretionary expenses. DP931 defines 'fixed' as trends that have a certain trend frequency period.

decisionPoints.title: Income type
decisionPoints.description: Decision Point 910 delivers the report group name of the main income (e.g. Salary, Benefits, Rental Income). The main income is the group of income transactions determined to have the largest Ongoing sum.

decisionPoints.title: Confidence
decisionPoints.description: Decision Point 911 delivers the level of certainty we've calculated for the trend of the main income. The possible values are 'certain' and 'uncertain'.

decisionPoints.title: Ongoing monthly amount
decisionPoints.description: Decision Point 952 delivers the Ongoing monthly amount for the main income. If no Ongoing amount is identified for the main income, a zero result will be displayed.

decisionPoints.title: Income has been stable for
decisionPoints.description: Decision Point 913 delivers the duration of the Ongoing trend for the main income. The period will be displayed as it matches the identified trend of the income and not normalised to your preferred period. If the main income does not have an Ongoing trend, this decision point will return 'None' as the value.

decisionPoints.title: Overall duration of income
decisionPoints.description: Decision Point 914 delivers the duration of the Overall trend for the main income. The period will be displayed as it matches the identified trend of the income and not normalised to your preferred period.

decisionPoints.title: Ongoing monthly amount
decisionPoints.description: Decision Point 953 delivers the Ongoing monthly amount for all of the identified income. If no Ongoing amount is identified for all income, a zero result will be displayed.

decisionPoints.title: # of trends
decisionPoints.description: Decision Point 916 delivers the count of trends for Ongoing identified income.

decisionPoints.title: % of amount uncertain
decisionPoints.description: Decision Point 917 delivers the percentage of Ongoing identified income trends that are uncertain.

decisionPoints.title: Ongoing monthly amount
decisionPoints.description: Decision Point 954 delivers the Ongoing monthly amount for all of the financial commitments. If no Ongoing amount is identified for financial commitments, a zero result will be displayed.

decisionPoints.title: # of trends
decisionPoints.description: Decision Point 919 delivers the count of Ongoing trends for all financial commitments.

decisionPoints.title: % of amount uncertain
decisionPoints.description: Decision Point 920 delivers the percentage of Ongoing financial commitments that have an uncertain trend.

decisionPoints.title: Total known credit card limit
decisionPoints.description: Decision Point 921 delivers the sum of all known credit card limits (e.g. if there are two credit card accounts each with a $500 limit, the result will be $1,000). DP921 can only include credit card accounts in its calculation when those accounts form part of the Credit Sense report - external accounts held by the customer will not be included in the calculation.

decisionPoints.title: # of credit cards with unidentified limits
decisionPoints.description: Decision Point 922 delivers the count of credit cards with an unknown credit limit. DP921 includes credit card accounts on the Credit Sense report where the credit limit was not provided with the account data and external accounts held by the customer where credit card repayments or other associated transactions have been identified.

decisionPoints.title: Rent & board monthly amount
decisionPoints.description: Decision Point 955 calculates the monthly rent and board expenditure.

decisionPoints.title: Essential spend monthly amount
decisionPoints.description: Decision Point 956 calculates the monthly essential expenditure. DP956 defines 'essential' spend as transactions matching our essential expenditure classification.

decisionPoints.title: % of essential spend that is fixed
decisionPoints.description: Decision Point 925 delivers the percentage of Ongoing essential expenditure that is fixed. DP925 defines 'fixed' as having a certain and stable trend frequency period and excludes Rent & Board.

decisionPoints.title: Discretionary spend monthly amount
decisionPoints.description: Decision Point 957 calculates the monthly discretionary expenditure. DP957 defines 'discretionary' spend as transactions matching our discretionary expenditure classification.

decisionPoints.title: % of discretionary spend that is fixed
decisionPoints.description: Decision Point 927 delivers the percentage of Ongoing discretionary expenditure that is fixed. DP927 defines 'fixed' as having a certain and stable trend frequency period.

decisionPoints.title: Ongoing monthly amount
decisionPoints.description: Decision Point 958 delivers the Ongoing monthly amount for credits identified as Possible Income. If no Ongoing amount is identified for Possible Income, a zero result will be displayed.

decisionPoints.title: Frequency of income
decisionPoints.description: Decision Point 933 delivers the trend frequency of the main income. If no Ongoing amount is identified for the main income, an empty result will be displayed.

decisionPoints.title: Next pay date
decisionPoints.description: Decision Point 934 delivers the projected next pay date for the main income. If no Ongoing amount is identified for the main income, an empty result will be displayed.

decisionPoints.title: Next pay amount
decisionPoints.description: Decision Point 935 delivers the projected next pay amount for the main income. If no Ongoing amount is identified for the main income, a zero result will be displayed.

decisionPoints.title: Average recent closing balance on day of main income
decisionPoints.description: Decision Point 936 delivers the average funds available on the day the customer receives their main income. DP936 delivers the mean closing balance on days the main income is paid into the main income account. It defines 'recent' as within 90 days of the end of the report.

decisionPoints.title: % of income withdrawn via ATM
decisionPoints.description: Decision Point 937 delivers the percentage of identified income that is withdrawn via ATM. DP937 calculates the result by dividing the sum of Ongoing ATM withdrawals by the sum of Ongoing identified income.

decisionPoints.title: # of recent financial dishonours
decisionPoints.description: Decision Point 938 delivers the count of financial dishonours that occurred within the most recent 90 days of the report period. DP938 includes both cleared and uncleared dishonours related to transactions with a 'financial' expenditure classification.

decisionPoints.title: % of income spent on High Risk Merchants
decisionPoints.description: Decision Point 939 delivers the percentage of income that is spent on High-Risk Merchants. DP939 calculates the result by dividing the sum of Ongoing High-Risk Merchant spend by the sum of Ongoing identified income.

decisionPoints.title: # of recent new sources of finance
decisionPoints.description: Decision Point 940 delivers the count of new sources of finance within the most recent 90 days of the report period. DP940 defines 'recent' as within the last 90 days of the report, 'new' as any trend that has started within the recent period, and 'sources of finance' as providers of loans rather than individual loans. It includes any transactions with a 'financial' expenditure classification.

decisionPoints.title: Has recent changes to income circumstances
decisionPoints.description: Decision Point 941 delivers a flag to indicate whether recent changes to the customer's income were identified. DP941 defines 'recent' as within the last 90 days of the report and 'changes' as any variation or difference in patterns greater than $100 that may indicate a change in employment or other income source.

decisionPoints.title: Has uncleared financial dishonours
decisionPoints.description: Decision Point 942 delivers a flag to indicate whether the customer has any financial dishonours that remain uncleared. DP942 defines dishonours as being 'uncleared' if there hasn't been a payment for the associated financial commitment since the dishonour occurred. It includes all dishonours related to transactions with a 'financial' expenditure classification.

decisionPoints.title: Has potential gambling withdrawals via ATM
decisionPoints.description: Decision Point 943 delivers a flag to indicate whether ATM withdrawal behaviour matches patterns known to be associated with gambling (i.e. making multiple withdrawals at the same ATM on the same day).

decisionPoints.title: Has received crisis support payments
decisionPoints.description: Decision Point 944 delivers a flag to indicate whether credits identified as crisis support payments have been identified within the report period.

decisionPoints.title: Has superannuation credits
decisionPoints.description: Decision Point 945 delivers a flag to indicate whether credits identified as superannuation have been identified within the report period.

decisionPoints.title: Has cash advances
decisionPoints.description: Decision Point 946 delivers a flag to indicate whether transactions identified as cash advances have been identified within the report period. DP946 defines cash advances as transfers from a credit card account to another account or cash withdrawals from a credit card account.

decisionPoints.title: Has redraws
decisionPoints.description: Decision Point 947 delivers a flag to indicate whether transactions identified as redraws have been identified within the report period. DP947 defines redraws as transfers from a loan account to another account or cash withdrawals from a loan account.

decisionPoints.title: Has High-Cost Finance
decisionPoints.description: Decision Point 948 delivers a flag to indicate whether transactions identified as High-Cost Finance have been identified within the report period.

decisionPoints.title: Missing essential expenses: groceries
decisionPoints.description: Decision Point 949 delivers a flag to indicate whether we believe there is missing grocery spend within the report period. DP949 will return a 'Yes' value if no Ongoing trends have been identified as groceries, indicating missing data or the possible presence of an additional account held by the customer for the purpose of grocery expenses.

decisionPoints.title: Missing essential expenses: transport
decisionPoints.description: Decision Point 950 delivers a flag to indicate whether we believe there is missing transport spend within the report period. DP950 will return a 'Yes' value if no Ongoing trends have been identified as transport, indicating missing data or the possible presence of an additional account held by the customer for the purpose of transport expenses.

decisionPoints.title: Missing essential expenses: accommodation
decisionPoints.description: Decision Point 951 delivers a flag to indicate whether we believe there is missing accommodation spend within the report period. DP951 will return a 'Yes' value if no Ongoing trends have been identified as accommodation, indicating missing data or the possible presence of an additional account held by the customer for the purpose of accommodation expenses.
